DTSTART;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260308T190000
DTEND;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260308T191500
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=SU
SUMMARY:Weekly ONE Thing Selection (15 min)
DESCRIPTION:Use the Focusing Question to choose next week's lead domino.\n\n"What's the ONE Thing I can do this week such that by doing it everything else will be easier or unnecessary?"\n\nWrite it down. Set Monday's ONE Thing block task. Done.\n\nThis should take 15 minutes maximum. If it takes longer, you're overthinking.
CATEGORIES:Planning,ONE Thing,Sunday
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT5M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Weekly ONE Thing Selection in 5 minutes — grab your Focusing Question
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jaye-os-nightly-reset-20260226@jayeos
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
DTSTART;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260226T213000
DTEND;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260226T214000
RRULE:FREQ=DAILY
SUMMARY:Nightly Reset (10 min)
DESCRIPTION:End-of-day reset — 10 minutes maximum.\n\n1. What was today's needle mover?\n2. What was the biggest energy leak?\n3. What must happen tomorrow?\n4. One instruction to tomorrow-you.\n5. Rate energy (1-10).\n6. Did you complete the ONE Thing block? (Y/N)\n\nLog in Notion Nightly Reset database. If this takes more than 10 minutes, it's broken.
CATEGORIES:Reset,Nightly,Review
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT5M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Nightly Reset in 5 minutes — wind down and reflect
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jaye-os-monthly-measurement-20260401@jayeos
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
DTSTART;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260401T140000
DTEND;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260401T150000
RRULE:FREQ=MONTHLY;BYMONTHDAY=1
SUMMARY:Monthly Measurement (60 min)
DESCRIPTION:First of the month — deep review.\n\n1. Review last month's ONE Thing — achieved or missed?\n2. What to kill this month (one thing that no longer serves you).\n3. What to systemise this month (one thing to make repeatable).\n4. Stress level (1-10).\n5. Revenue check (optional).\n6. Decision: Expand / Stabilise / Reduce.\n\nUpdate Monthly Measurement database in Notion.\n\nRule: one kill + one systemise decision per month. No more.
CATEGORIES:Monthly,Review,Measurement
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Monthly Measurement in 30 minutes — prepare your data
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jaye-os-quarterly-reset-20260601@jayeos
DTSTAMP:20260226T000000Z
DTSTART;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260601T090000
DTEND;TZID=Australia/Sydney:20260601T110000
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY;BYMONTH=1,4,7,10;BYMONTHDAY=1
SUMMARY:Quarterly Reset (2 hours)
DESCRIPTION:Quarterly strategic reset — 2 hours of deep thinking.\n\n1. Diagnosis: What is the binding constraint right now?\n2. Guiding policy: What is the one policy that addresses it?\n3. Coherent actions: What are the 3 (max) actions that execute the policy?\n4. Operator load vs Architect load — where are you vs target?\n5. One leverage decision that permanently reduces operator load.\n6. Set next quarter's ONE Thing.\n\nUpdate Quarterly Reset database in Notion.\n\nThis is strategy, not planning. Think in constraints and leverage, not tasks.
CATEGORIES:Quarterly,Strategy,Reset
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT60M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Quarterly Reset in 1 hour — clear your schedule and prepare
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT

END:VCALENDAR
